ame":"Abbes","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Arabic/Muslim Syed, Ghulam, Ali, Mohammad, Mohammed, Mohamed, Farhat, Abbas, Asad, Azhar, Ahmad, Amir.","Muslim: from the Arabic personal name <i>ʿAbbās</i>, literally ‘stern, austere’. Al-ʿAbbas ibn ʿAbd al-Muttalib was the name of an uncle of the prophet Muhammad (see   Abbasi  ).","Dutch: patronymic from the personal name <i>Abbe</i>, a pet form of   Albert   or   Albrecht  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Abbasi","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Arabic/Muslim Mohammad, Ali, Abdul, Adnan, Tariq, Arshad, Mahmood, Mohammed, Mousa, Muhammad, Nadeem, Sami.","Muslim (Indian subcontinent and Iran): surname denoting descent from or association with someone called   Abbas  , in particular association with Al-‘Abbas ibn ‘Abd al-Muttalib, an uncle (died 652) of the prophet Muhammad, the ancestor of the Abbasid dynasty of caliphs, who ruled the Islamic world from 750 to 1258."]},{"name":"Abas","meanings":["Muslim: variant of   Abbas  ."]}]},{"name":"David","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, borne by the greatest of all the kings of Israel, whose history is recounted with great vividness in the first and second books of Samuel and elsewhere. As a boy he killed the giant Philistine Goliath with his slingshot. As king of Judah, and later of all Israel, he expanded the power of the Israelites and established the security of their kingdom. He was also noted as a poet, many of the Psalms being attributed to him. The Hebrew derivation of the name is uncertain; it is said by some to represent a nursery word meaning ‘darling’. It is a very popular Jewish name, but is almost equally common among Gentiles in the English-speaking world. It is particularly common in Wales and Scotland, having been borne by the patron saint of Wales (  see  Dewi   ) and by two medieval kings of Scotland."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":5,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"David Abbes was born in 1450, in Suffolk, England. He had at least 1 son with Elizabeth Goodwyn. He died in 1543, in Essex, England, at the age of 93."},"et":{"1450–1543":"1450–1543","1480–1523":"1480–1523","1495–1554":"1495–1554","1523":"1523","1543":"1543","1455":"1455","1554":"1554","1495":"1495","1450":"1450","1480":"1480","Nayland, Suffolk, England":"Nayland, Suffolk, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Essex, England":"Essex, England"},"fi":{"1450–1543":"1450–1543","1480–1523":"1480–1523","1495–1554":"1495–1554","1523":"1523","1543":"1543","1455":"1455","1554":"1554","1495":"1495","1450":"1450","1480":"1480","Nayland, Suffolk, England":"Nayland, Suffolk, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Essex, England":"Essex, England"},"fr":{"1450–1543":"1450–1543","1480–1523":"1480–1523","1495–1554":"1495–1554","1523":"1523","1543":"1543","1455":"1455","1554":"1554","1495":"1495","1450":"1450","1480":"1480","Nayland, Suffolk, England":"Nayland, Suffolk, Angleterre","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Angleterre","Essex, England":"Essex, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"David Abbes est né en 1450, à Suffolk, Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Elizabeth Goodwyn. Il est décédé en 1543, à Essex, Angleterre, à l’âge de 93 ans."},"de":{"1450–1543":"1450–1543","1480–1523":"1480–1523","1495–1554":"1495–1554","1523":"1523","1543":"1543","1455